!! Creating a help page (static)

```
title: $:/plugins/rimir/my-plugin/llm-help/my-topic
tags: $:/tags/rimir/llm-help/page
llm-help-path: my-plugin/my-topic
llm-help-description: Description shown in parent listings
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Content the LLM will read when it navigates to this path.
```

!! Multi-path page

Mount the same content at two paths:

```
llm-help-path: data-model/person/create actions/create/person
```

The LLM reaches this page whether it navigates via `data-model` or `actions/create`.

!! Dynamic page (reading domain schema)

```
title: $:/plugins/your-plugin/llm-help/type-person
tags: $:/tags/rimir/llm-help/page
llm-help-path: data-model/person
llm-help-description: Person type — fields, constraints, creation, search
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

<$importvariables filter="[[$:/plugins/your-plugin/llm-help/type-info-macro]]">
<<render-type-info "person">>
</$importvariables>
```

The macro can read your plugin's schema definitions and render field info dynamically.

!! Context-restricted page

Only visible when the active context includes `rimir/appify`:

```
llm-help-context: rimir/appify
```

Only visible in a specific app:

```
llm-help-context: orga-view
```

!! User shortcut

Created via the settings UI or manually:

```
title: $:/llm-help/user/create-person-shortcut
tags: $:/tags/rimir/llm-help/page
llm-help-path: shortcuts/create-person
llm-help-description: Quick guide to creating a person
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

1. Find the parent org: search_tiddlers with rrt.type=orga
2. Create person: create_tiddler with basetitle=<org>/pn:<abbrev>
3. Set fields: caption, abbrev, parent, status
```

